<HEADLINE>
BUSINESS TAX, HOUSE TAX CAN BE PAID AT CONVENIENCE STORES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 28 (CNA) 04/28/07  18:48:32 (By Y.F. Low)
</P>
<P>
Taxpayers can now pay their business tax and house tax at
designated convenience stores from this year if payment due does
not exceed NT$20,000 (US$602) , Taipei National Tax
Administration officials said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The business tax will be collected from May 1-10 and the house
tax will be collected from May 1-31, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
They said more than 29,000 small businesses with a turnover of
below NT$200,000 per month in Taipei now see their business taxes
amount to no more than NT$20,000.
</P>
<P>
The stores that can collect payments include Hi-Life, Family
Mart, Nikomart, 7-Eleven and OK, which have a total of more than
8,000 outlets around the country, they added.
</P>
